\mt1 SAMUEL CABU  
\mt3 A Pacuek Nah  
\mt4 (The First Book of Samuel)  
\is1 Samuel Cabu Pacuek Kawng  
\im Lamhma ah tah Samuel Pacuek neh Pabae he Cabu khat la om. 1080 to 970 \sc b.c.\sc* Israel ca rhoek kah khokhuen neh cil te a tueng sak tih tonghma Samuel a cunnah lamloh manghai David a dueknah hill a daek. He cabu dongah Israel ram a moecuek vaengkah thinom Samuel, Saul neh David kawng om. Israel ca rhoek te amah koca rhoek kah mawtnah laitloek nah voevoeh hma tih manghai mawtnah ben la cet.  
\ip Lamhma cuek la Samuel kah a thangnah, Pathen loh a khue nah, tonghma neh camtloek boeilu la a omnah kawng a thui. Namtom bangla pilnam loh amih aka mawtkung ham manghai a hoe uh. Te vaengah Pathen loh Samuel la, “Benjamin koca lamkah,” a ti nah. Saul neh Pathen loh a ngaihaknah hmanah Boeipa ol te Saul loh ngai pawh. Te dongah Saul te manghai lamloh a paa sak tih David a tuek sak. Saul loh David te thunkha rhalcak bangla a khueh vaengah David he Samuel loh a bom. Samuel Cabu a pacuek he Philistin kut ah Saul pacaphung a dueknah neh a bawt sak. Samuel cabu a pabae dongah tah David kawng a tael. Samuel Cabu he \sc b.c \sc* 930 tluk vaengah boeih tael coi ni a ti.  
\iot Sawt Yoeinah  
\io1 Samuel \ior 1. 1—7. 17\ior*  
\io1 Saul \ior 8. 1—15. 35 \ior*  
\io1 David \ior 16. 1—31. 13\ior*  
\c 1  
\s1 Hannah kah Olhlo  
\p
